title: For Sale:  CZ SP-01 9mm for SALE!
postcontent: I have for sale a pristine, very lightly used CZ SP-01 in 9mm with a few Cajun Gun Works upgrades installed. This gun is a all steel, 9mm slinging beast on the range with impressive accuracy and negligible recoil. Makes an outstanding home defense and range gun. This SP-01 has been meticulously maintained and cleaned after every outing. Only the magazines show any real wear (CZ mags show bluing wear fast!) Has ambidextrious manual safties, Tru-Dot night sights, and two factory 18 round magazines with Wolf extra power mag springs installed. The gun also has Cajun Gun Works excellent Ultra-Lite Kit, consisting of their extended firing pin, 13lb mainspring (with extra 11lb for range and competition), firing pin spring, and firing pin block spring. Also has a CZ Custom solid firing pin retaining pin, and CGW 14lb. recoil spring, stronger trigger return spring and floating trigger pin (which makes replacement of triggers and springs much easier). Add on a weapon light and this is a serious HD pistol platform. All of the factory parts I removed are included. I have shot about 400 rounds of various ammo makes; 124gr. Gold Dot & Hydra-shok hollowpoints, as well as 115 & 124gr. Winchester White Box FMJ, Sellior & Beloit, Blazer Brass, and Tula steel case ammo without a single malfunction. CZ's typically get the best accuracy with 124gr. ammo. If I didn't need to thin out my herd in favor of smaller carry guns I would never part with her since she is the most accurate 9mm I've ever owned.Price is $600 cash only, no tradesI will meet at the Everything Weapons parking lot in Cool Springs area of Franklin, TN. Must have a valid TN Carry Permit as proof of identity (and as a state funded background check!). Will have a Bill of Sale to sign for both of us.If interested text me at REDACTED

title: For Sale/Trade:  Burgsmuller & Kreiensen Combination/Drilling
postcontent: This is a "combination gun" known as a drilling. It has two 16 gauge shotgun barrels with a single 7x57 mm rifle barrel. The gun is in good condition and functions flawlessly. Has two triggers that are controlled by a safety switch located right below the barrel release switch. When centered, the safety switch is on "safe", when switched to the right the two shotgun barrels are controlled by the two triggers just as any other double barrel shotgun. When switched to the left, the rear sight pops up for the rifle, and the front trigger controls the firing pin for the rifle barrel; the rear trigger still controls the left shotgun barrel. These firearms are perfect for people living on farms or with large tracts of land, because they conveniently have shotgun and rifle cartridges for any type of game. I personaly have done some reasearch on the 7x57 mm cartridge and it is an "all around" cartridge easily capable of taking down large game. Please contact me if you have more questions.

postcontent:
Up for sale, is my New In Box (never fired) Russian Izhmash Saiga 7.62x39, Converted to standard AKM buttstock and pistol grip configuration by Century Arms, in limited numbers.  Century put their own signature vent cuts to the front handguard, for a more tactical look.  This is the popular Russian rifle which was banned from import by the Obama administration, and price has climbed exponentially for.  It’s the last real chance to buy an authentic Russian AKM at this price, as the value only continues to go up, and no more will probably ever come in (like the Chinese ban in 1994)! 
It is built off an imported 2009 Russian Saiga IZ132 Sporter Rifle in 7.62x39.  Imported by the RWC Group, it was sold to Century Arms, who performed a back-end conversion on the sporter rifle, and gave it an item number of RI1808E-N.  The conversion turns it from a sporter configuration, into its current original AKM configuration by moving the fire control group further back in the receiver, installing an AKM pistol grip and buttstock, as well as installing a bullet guide to allow feed of the double stack AKM magazines.  Century also needs to completely refinish the receiver due to the moving of the fire control group, and subsequent moving of retaining pins/holes.  The conversion process is difficult for most to do at home, and is expensive to have professionally done - so this particular rifle gets you an authentic Russian AKM without all the fuss!Specifications:

title: For Sale:  Early Kimber .338 Win Mag
postcontent: Back when Kimber of Oregon's Greg Warne sold the financially ailing Kimber company name to it's present owners, the sale price having been met, left it's new owners short of the funds to move the company to Yonkers New York, and have sufficient funds to tool up for production there. The new company invested what funds they could in the purchase of WWI and WWII Mausers. They bought a larger number of Swedish model 96 Mausers which they sporterized as Kimber 96's . These guns were stocked in inexpensive synthetic stocks, and sold at reasonable prices in order to raise funds for the company's tooling up to build the 1911 Colt pistol design, under the Kimber name. Along with the Swedish model 96's a smaller number of WWII VZ24 Mauser 98's in surplus condition were purchased, and re-barreled as sporterized guns with synthetic stocks. The 98's were cobbled up as 7mm Rem &338 Winchester magnums and shipped, in large part, to Alaska for sale there as economical hunting pieces. This beautiful .338 Win Mag is just to hard for me to handle. It's sighted in and is a tack driver. It also comes with 4 boxes of ammo (not shown). If you've looked the ammo alone is worth $200 so this is a great deal.

He makes the blades puts them together and then sends them out to be black onodized. I was in his blacksmith shop one day and he had a load of knives, all bright, ready to go to the anodizer. I said" hey Chuck, why don't you sell me one of those knives bright before it gets to the anodizer. He did some hemming and hawing but finally sold me the knife....meaning I have a one of a kind of the Ox Forge switch blade. Before you pass on this, do some research of Charles, you will find out he is a Master Bladesmith, he is Black Smith making knives worth several thousand dollars, plus his military contract for the switchblades, he was embedded with the Special Forces in Iraq, and the list goes on.
